  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`evm.gasEstimates` is an output offered in Solidity's JSON standard output. We already expose this information in the ABI, so it should be easy to tweak and produce output that's compatible with how Solidity delivers it.\r\n\r\nHere's the example output from their [documentation](https://solidity.readthedocs.io/en/v0.6.8/using-the-compiler.html#output-description)..  ours won't say \"infinite\" of course :)\r\n\r\n```json\r\n\"gasEstimates\": {\r\n    \"creation\": {\r\n        \"codeDepositCost\": \"420000\",\r\n        \"executionCost\": \"infinite\",\r\n        \"totalCost\": \"infinite\"\r\n    },\r\n    \"external\": {\r\n        \"delegate(address)\": \"25000\"\r\n    },\r\n    \"internal\": {\r\n        \"heavyLifting()\": \"infinite\"\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
